006.","meanings":["Originally a variant of   Adelaide  , representing an Old French spelling of a reduced form of Germanic <i>Adalheidis</i>. <i>Alice</i> and <i>Adelaide</i> were already regarded as distinct names in English during the medieval period. <i>Alice</i> enjoyed a surge of popularity in the 19th century and periods of favour ever since. It was the name of the central character of  Lewis Carroll's  Alice's Adventures in Wonderland (  1865 ) and Through the Looking Glass (  1872 ), who was based on his child friend  Alice Liddell , daughter of the Dean of Christ Church, Oxford."],"variants":[{"name":"Alys","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Alice ."]},{"name":"Alis","meanings":["equivalent of <b>Alice</b> ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Mrs. Alice Helyon was born about 1213, in England, United Kingdom. She had at least 1 son with Walter de Helyon."},"et":{"about 1213–":"umbes 1213–Surnud","1208–Male":"1208–Surnud","1233–1300":"1233–1300","1213–Female":"1213–Surnud","1213":"1213","1300":"1300","1233":"1233","about 1213":"umbes 1213","about 1233":"umbes 1233","1208":"1208","England, United Kingdom":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"about 1213–":"noin 1213–Kuollut","1208–Male":"1208–Kuollut","1233–1300":"1233–1300","1213–Female":"1213–Kuollut","1213":"1213","1300":"1300","1233":"1233","about 1213":"noin 1213","about 1233":"noin 1233","1208":"1208","England, United Kingdom":"Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"about 1213–":"environ 1213–Décédée","1208–Male":"1208–Décédé","1233–1300":"1233–1300","1213–Female":"1213–Décédée","1213":"1213","1300":"1300","1233":"1233","about 1213":"environ 1213","about 1233":"environ 1233","1208":"1208","England, United Kingdom":"Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Mrs. Alice Helyon est née environ 1213, à Angleterre, Royaume-Uni. Elle a eu au moins 1 fils avec Walter de Helyon."},"de":{"about 1213–":"um 1213–Verstorben","1208–Male":"1208–Verstorben","1233–1300":"1233–1300","1213–Female":"1213–Verstorben","1213":"1213","1300"